candidates.body: Fixes #371.

candidates.title: Update -sys version number and Rust version
Fixes version in tss-esapi crate on main.
candidates.body: - Sets the version of the the tss-esapi crate to 8.0.0-alpha on the main branch in order to avoid confusion.

candidates.title: Improves handling of ```size_t``` FFI values.
candidates.body:
- The size_t type that is used in all the MU APIs will be dependent on the compiler that ```bindgen``` uses to generate the bindings for the library. This attempts to make the crate less dependant on that value in the public APIs.
- Changes the Marshall and Unmarshall traits to use usize as input.
- Fixes #469

candidates.title: Add serde to Public and Private
candidates.body: Add support for serde to Public and Private, going through the current Marshall and Unmarshall pathways. This pattern is quite "simple" so it could be possible to duplicate it to other structures, or macro them for types that implement Marshall and Unmarshall.

candidates.title: Bump picky- crates
candidates.body:
A recent fix [1] in the picky-asn1-der crate highlights an issue that could lead to faulty results handed off by the abstractions in the tss-esapi crate. Specifically, mishandling of ASN.1 Integers could result in invalid encodings of various pieces of data such as elliptic curve points.

[1] https://github.com/Devolutions/picky-rs/pull/209/files

candidates.title: Fixes problem with lint warnings in different versions of Rust.
candidates.body: - The crate supports several different versions of rust and in some of these versions the Clippy lint tool introduces new warnings that are not present in previous versions of rust. This causes a warning when compiling. This has been fixed in this commit by using the `rustversion` crate to only add the lint if the crate is being built with a version of Rust that has it.

candidates.title: Adds strum as a integration test requirement.
candidates.body:
-Adds integration-test feature in order to conditionally add
 dependencies.

-Updates the TpmFormatZeroWarning so it is possible to iterate over all
 the items when creating integration tests.

candidates.title: Add example for hmac
candidates.body: Relates to #21 - This adds an example of how to create a loadable hmac key.

candidates.title: Add `abstraction` feature
candidates.body: Adding a feature that separates the abstraction from the basic interface of the Rust-native crate. This feature is enabled by default so as not to break existing uses.
